name: Israel
summary: Tensions between Israel and Iran have escalated following an apparent Israeli strike on Iran. The strike, on Iran's Isfahan province, has been confirmed by Iranian state media with explosions also being reported at an airport in central Iran. Iran has vowed an "immediate and maximum level" response to any Israeli attack, while the United States has imposed new sanctions on Iran after an attack on Israel. Israel has not officially confirmed its involvement in the strike, but British Foreign Minister David Cameron has stated that Israel has decided to retaliate against Iran. Amid heightened tensions, Iran's attack on Israel has sparked debate, with some claiming it was not as unsuccessful as initially believed and has broken Israel's isolation. However, others have emphasized the need for calm and de-escalation, with US Secretary of State Antony Blinken calling for restraint.

name: F1
summary: Formula 1 is back in China after a three-year hiatus, with the first sprint race of the season taking place. The season also sees a significant format shake-up, with the introduction of six sprint races and a revised points system. Despite concerns from some drivers, fans are expected to benefit from the changes. Additionally, F1 has released its first impact report, detailing its progress in sustainability. The 2024 Chinese Grand Prix will be held on April 14th, with qualifying, sprint, and race details available for Australian viewers. Amidst the excitement, Max Verstappen expressed frustration with a chaotic qualifying session, while Lando Norris shone under pressure. In other news, Daniel Ricciardo has admitted his contract situation is uncertain, and a team has denied Ricciardo exerted undue influence in a driver lineup switch ahead of the Chinese GP. Fans can engage with F1 through the Fantasy league, where they can compete against driver Zhou Guanyu.

IGN finds it "a frustratingly unrewarding experience," acknowledging its ambitious visuals but ultimately finding its narrative lacking. USA TODAY provides a practical guide on how to access the film in Australia, while Den of Geek offers a recap of the first part and anticipates the release of the second. summary: In Round 7 of the 2024 NRL season, the newly founded Dolphins took on the Parramatta Eels in an unexpected thrashing. The Dolphins stunned the Eels with a record-breaking display, securing a dominant 44-16 victory.
